HEADWORD: Pentacrinus
<hw>Pen*tac"ri*nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Penta-</er>, and <er>Crinum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
genus of large, stalked crinoids, of which several species occur in deep
water among the West Indies and elsewhere.</def>⟦br⟧
